<div class="FunctionDoc YAMLDoc" id="basejoystick-flush" markdown="1">

## [function __basejoystick.flush__()](#function-__basejoystickflush__) {#function-__basejoystickflush__}

Clears all pending input, not limited to the joystick.

__Returns:__

True if joyinput was pending (i.e., if there was something to flush) and False otherwise.

- Type: bool

</div>

[basejoystick.flush]: #basejoystick-flush
[flush]: #basejoystick-flush

<div class="FunctionDoc YAMLDoc" id="basejoystick-get_joyaxes" markdown="1">

## [function __basejoystick.get_joyaxes__(timeout=None)](#function-__basejoystickget_joyaxes__timeoutnone) {#function-__basejoystickget_joyaxes__timeoutnone}

Waits for joystick axes movement.

__Keywords:__

- `timeout` -- A timeout value in milliseconds or `None` to use default timeout.
	- Default: None
	- Type: int, float, NoneType

__Returns:__

A (position, timestamp) tuple. The position is None if a timeout occurs.

- Type: tuple

</div>

