<div class="FunctionDoc YAMLDoc" id="basejoystick-get_joyinput" markdown="1">

## [function __basejoystick.get_joyinput__(joybuttonlist=None, timeout=None)](#function-__basejoystickget_joyinput__joybuttonlistnone-timeoutnone) {#function-__basejoystickget_joyinput__joybuttonlistnone-timeoutnone}

Waits for any joystick input (buttons, axes, hats or balls).

__Keywords:__

- `joybuttonlist` -- A list of buttons that are accepted or `None` to default joybuttonlist.
	- Default: None
	- Type: list, NoneType
- `timeout` -- A timeout value in milliseconds or `None` to use default timeout.
	- Default: None
	- Type: int, float, NoneType

__Returns:__

A (event, value, timestamp) tuple. The value is `None` if a timeout occurs.

- Type: tuple

</div>

[basejoystick.get_joyinput]: #basejoystick-get_joyinput
[get_joyinput]: #basejoystick-get_joyinput

<div class="FunctionDoc YAMLDoc" id="basejoystick-input_options" markdown="1">

## [function __basejoystick.input_options__()](#function-__basejoystickinput_options__) {#function-__basejoystickinput_options__}

Generates a list with the number of available buttons, axes, balls and hats.

__Returns:__

A list with number of inputs as: [buttons, axes, balls,
hats].

- Type: list

</div>

